passages.text:
Jasper,head_tilted::...

Wiggly,neutral::This is where you'll be staying.  Forever, I think.

Jasper,surprised::...

Wiggly,surprised::I'm not as smart as a lot of the people who worked here, or some of the people who come through.  But I see some things clearly.

Wiggly,skeptical::Even when we were just walking through the halls, or sitting alone in the boilers, I could feel you worming into me.

Jasper,sad::...

Wiggly,sad::I feel bad, but I still have time left.  I have life.

Wiggly,thinking::That's a lot more than many people ever get, you know?

Wiggly,looking_to_side::It's more than most people have right now.  Most people are dead, forever.

Jasper,thinking::...

Wiggly,looking_to_side::Some people didn't treat me kindly.  But I'm not going to let them take away the rest of what I have.

Wiggly,surprised::And I'm not going to let you take it away either.

Jasper,surprised::...

Wiggly,neutral::I brought you here because I'm nice.  I thought it seemed like a good spot, to rest.

Wiggly,surprised::I know you mean well.

Wiggly,skeptical::But you aren't coming with me.  Amelie is better off without you, too.

Jasper,sad::...

Wiggly,neutral::I have a client to get home.  She might be my last.  I hope she's still waiting for me.

Wiggly,looking_to_side::Goodbye, Jasper.

Jasper,sad::...

Jasper,sad::....

Jasper,sad::.....

passages.text:
Wiggly,looking_to_side::Here we are.
